- The integer array parameter `rects` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `rects` must contain non-overlapping axis-aligned rectangles.
- The integer array parameter `rects` must have each rectangle defined by four integer values `[a, b, x, y]` where `(a, b)` is the bottom-left corner point and `(x, y)` is the top-right corner point.
- The integer array parameter `rects` must have each rectangle with dimensions such that `x - a <= 2000` and `y - b <= 2000`.
- The integer array parameter `rects` must have each rectangle with coordinates such that `-10^9 <= a < x <= 10^9` and `-10^9 <= b < y <= 10^9`.
- The integer array parameter `rects` must not have overlapping rectangles.
- The integer array parameter `rects` must have at most 10^4 calls to the `pick` method.
- The `Solution` class must be initialized with the given rectangles `rects`.
- The `pick` method must return a random integer point `[u, v]` inside the space covered by one of the given rectangles.